title: For Sale:  Winchester 1894 takedown rifle 30WCF
postcontent: This is a 30-30 Model 94 takedown rifle with 26" round barrel and a 2/3 (16") magazine tube. The gun was manufactured in 1908. The left side of barrel is marked "nickel steel barrel" especially for smokeless powder. The circle WP proof marks are on top of barrel and receiver but the receiver is double stamped as shown in photo. The rear sight is a Marbles flip-up sight with the white diamond screw adjuster insert. The front sight is marked Marble #5. The stock is a standard straight grip uncheckered wood that has some figure and a crescent steel butt plate. The wood is still proud of the metal but there is a crack at right frong by receiver as shown in photo. The stock is sound with minor nicks and dings. The stock has small holes on both sides that were probably from a plaque or a decoration at some time. (photo) The forend is sound with some burl wood appearance and is the proper 9 1/2" with metal nosecap. The top of the forend has small broken area by the endcap, probably due to the figured wood not having much strength in thin area. Endcap is a gray patina. Very fine condition barrel and magazine tube have most of original blue with a few typical minor nicks and scratches. The barrel has blue wear on top between rear sight and receiver as shown. The receiver and takedown ring are a blended gray patina. Hammer has some blue color. The lever shows blended dark patina. The mechanics are crisp and lock-up is tight. The barrel has a shiny bore with no pitting or rings, probably has not had much use. The gun is sold with an old takedown padded case.

title: For Sale:  2,500-Gallon Water Filtration System
postcontent:
Be prepared with this 2-Bucket water filtration system that will filter 2,500-gallons of water.  The system utilizes a gravity fed Talia Superdome filter with a 5-gallon catch reservoir.  The buckets and spigot used in the system are constructed of food-grade material and built with human consumption as the top priority.  

Talia Superdome filters have been uniquely designed to help save lives in third world countries that have the harshest and poorest water quality in the world. They have limited access to electricity or pressurized water delivery.

Talia Superdome gravity water filters are capable of filtering water from lakes, streams, rivers,ponds and virtually any dirty water into safe clean drinking water. This makes our Superdome filters the filter of choice for missionaries, disater relief organizations,emergencies,camping general preparedness and just plain simple cost effective drinking water. (less than 2 cents a gallon)

Talia Superdome filters, filter out harmful cysts, bad bacteria(Giardia,Cryptosporidum,E-Coli,Klebstella) which produce water bourne diseases capable of producing severe diarrhea leading to dehydration and in severe cases can cause death. Children are especially vulnerable with their little immune systems just starting to develop. (4,000-5,000 children die each day from water borne diseases) The elderly also struggle with compromised immune systems.

Talia Superdome filters help save lives by utilizing a fine pore ceramic water filter that is 3" x 5" (.3 micron) This design helps give a better flow rate and more contact time with the water for better filtration then some of the competitors out there. We utilize a stainless steel cap to eliminate leakage and breakage which has been a significant problem with some other companies.

Talia Superdome filters have been dipped in a silver solution to retard bacterial growth.

While filtering out all the harmful pathogens the Superdome filter has been filled with a the highest grade of silver impregnated granular activated coconut shell carbon on the market.

This really sets us apart where many of the competitors have no GAC in their filters let alone cocunut shell carbon. This gives these filters a 3,000 gallon capacity.

Granular activated carbon best known as (GAC) is the most powerful absorbent we have found. Granular activated carbon filters generally have a higher contaminant removal ratio. The two most important factors affecting the efficiency of activated carbon filtration are the amount of carbon in the unit and the amount of time the contaminant spends in contact with it. The longer the carbon is in contact with the water the better it is. Similarly, the lower the flow rate of the water, the more time the water is in contact with the filter. It is commonly used for removing organic constituents and residual disinfectants in water supplies. Typical surface area for activated carbon is approximately 1,000 square meters per gram (m2/gm.). The two principal mechanisms by which activated carbon remove contaminants from water are catalytic which removes residual disinfectants, and adsorption removes organics. Activated carbon filters are usually rated by the size of the particles they are able to remove, measured in microns, and generally range from 50 microns (least effective) down to 0.5 microns (Most effective). While coconut shell carbon typically costs 20% more than the others (bituminous, wood), it is generally regarded as the most effective of the three.

Activated carbon filters remove/reduce many volatile organic chemicals, pesticides and herbicides, as well as chlorine, benzene, trihalomethane compounds, radon, solvents and hundreds of other man-made chemicals found in tap water.

The two most important factors affecting the efficiency of activated carbon filtration are the amount of activated carbon in the unit and the amount of time the contaminant spends in contact with it. The more carbon the better. Particle size also affects contaminant removal rates.

ORGANIC REMOVAL
Most organics are more readily adsorbed and less soluble at a lower pH, and as the pH increases, removal decreases. It is recommended to increase the size of the carbon bed by twenty percent for every pH unit above neutral (7.0). Carbon filter capacity can be roughly estimated at 0 1 pound of organics per 1 pound of carbon at a flow rate of 1 to 2 gallons per minute per cubic foot and a bed depth of 3 feet.

RESIDUAL DISINFECTANTS REMOVAL
Activated carbon acts as a reducing agent and can remove and destroy residual disinfectants (chlorine and chloramine) through a catalytic reduction reaction. Where removal of organics by activated carbon takes minutes, removal of chlorine takes seconds. The chlorine capacity of a new activated carbon is: 1 pound of chlorine per pound of carbon at a flow rate of 3 to 5 cu. ft. and a bed depth of 3 feet. Chloramine in our city water supplies is monochloramine and is a much slower reaction.

FLOW RATE
Flow rate is going to be dependent on the number of (GAC) Granular Activated Carbon filters you have installed into your container. Generally the lower the flow rate, the more time the contaminant will have to diffuse into a pore and be adsorbed. Adsorption by activated carbon is almost always improved by a longer contact time. Lower temperatures seem to favor adsorption.

title: For Sale:  Colt LE-6940 AR15
postcontent:
Colt is commonly regarded as producing the best AR-15s and the LE 6940 is their top of the line model. It uses a monolithic upper which is machined from a large single aluminum block instead of most AR15s which have extruded rails bolted on. The advantages are:

Improved accuracy - the rails don't contact the barrel throwing off accuracy. Also because the rail is continuous, you don't have to use cantilevered mounts when mounting long scopes, making for a more rigid optics platform. Also when mounting lasers, they stay truer to the bore axis.
A more rigid platform with fewer parts to break, work loose, or lose.

In addition to being the top of the line commercially made AR15, this is the most desirable LE6940. This LE-6940 and it is 100% NEW IN BOX. It has never been fired or even had a magazine inserted into it.

My truck died last November and I originally listed a few items to raise money to get it fixed or get another truck. title: For Sale:  Rare Colt Pen Gun (.38 cal.) Tear Gas Firing
postcontent:
Purchased in Memphis in the late 1960’s. New, in original dealer box with cardstock header intact (original price: $6.95). Made by Colt in Hartford, CT. Pen gun is stamped “COLT” (see pic). 

Pen gun comes with original box, foam lining, 2 original, unused CS tear gas rounds and mounting bracket with screw for attaching under desk, at bedside, etc.

Cartridges are screwed onto the muzzle of the pen and the cocking knob pulled back and locked into position. To fire, simply thumb the knob down and the internal spring drives the firing pin into the primer.   

THIS DOES NOT FIRE PROJECTILES/BULLETS. It is manufactured for gas cartridges only. Conversion to fire live ammo is not recommended.

This is classified as a non-lethal weapon, but not as an AOW (Any Other Weapon), thus the buyer would not need any paperwork to own the pen gun (if the gun were converted by a Class 2 manufacturer to fire live ammo, it would need to be registered with the BATFE and a $5.00 tax stamp would be required).   

Incredible collector’s item. It is becoming increasingly rare to find these. I found two at auction going for 350+ each...

Buyer must be over 18 years of age and please check local laws before considering purchase. 

Price is firm. If shipping is required, buyer must agree to pay shipping cost. I ship only to the lower 48 states.
